This recipe will teach you how to prepare a delicious, salted caramel chocolate cake that is quick and easy to make and taste of chocolate paradise as well. The family is sure to love this treat! Enjoy… Ingredients: Cake - 250g butter - 300ml castor sugar - 5 extra large eggs - 400ml cake flour - 10ml baking powder - 180ml cocoa powder - 80ml milk  Ingredients: Filling - 1 tin of caramel treat - a generous pinch of sea salt flakes Ingredients: Choc Ganache - 200g dark chocolate - 125ml cream READ: Super moist gluten free Beetroot Brownies - recipe Instructions: Cake 1. Cream the butter and castor sugar together until light and creamy. 2. Add the eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. 3. Sift the flour, baking powder and cocoa together. 4. Add to the creamed mixture alternately with the milk. 5. Spoon the mixture into two 20cm cake pans lined with greaseproof paper and sprayed with non-stick cooking spray. 6. Bake in a preheated oven at 180°C for 25-30 minutes. 7. Cool for 10 minutes in the pan before turning out onto a cooling rack. 8. Sandwich the cakes together with half the salted caramel filling. 9. Transfer the rest to a piping bag. 10. Spread the chocolate topping over the cake, then pipe with the rest of the salted caramel. READ: Delicious dairy-free dishes - recipes Instructions: Filling 1. Mix together the caramel and salt until smooth. Instructions: Topping 1. Combine the chocolate and cream and heat over a gentle heat until melted and smooth. 2. Refrigerate for 10 minutes and then beat with an electric beater until light and fluffy.